    "description": "If you're a passionate Senior Doctor with drive and ambition, Biocon Digital Technologies in Varanasi is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Biocon Digital Technologies:\nBiocon Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Learning & development budget\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Biocon Digital Technologies!",
